* ''Q. Aurelii Symmachi quae supersunt'', ed. by [[Otto_Seeck|Otto Seeck]] (Berlin, 1883; reprinted Munich, 2001), ISBN 3-921575-19-2. All surviving writings of Symmachus: letters, speeches and official reports, in the original Latin. This volume is Volume 6 of the series [[Monumenta_Germaniae_Historica|Monumenta Germaniae Historica]].  The letters are also published in a supplementary volume XIII in the [[Patrologia_Latina|Patrologia Latina]]. More recently, ''Symmaque: Lettres'', ed. by [[Jean-Pierre_Callu|Jean-Pierre Callu]] in four volumes (Paris, 1972–2002) published by [[Budé|Les Belles Lettres]] contains the letters of Symmachus in Latin with facing-page French translation. This has the fullest text and translation.
